                                         JOHANNESBURG - A policeman has been shot in Protea North in a hijacking. It’s understood three gunmen approached the officer who was on duty in Soweto and shot him once in the leg and fled. Police say the hijackers then abandoned the unmarked police vehicle. Spokesperson Vincent Mashiteng said: “During the struggle, they actually shot him once in the leg. The police vehicle, they actually dumped it around the area a few meters away from the scene. We realised that even the officer’s firearm, they took his firearm and also his cellphone.”